### Phase 1: Backend Setup & AI Integration (Node.js & Express)
1. Setup an Express route: `POST /api/analyze`.
2. Use `multer` to handle a single file upload in memory (`multer.memoryStorage()`).
3. Extract the text content of the uploaded file (JavaScript/TypeScript).
4. Construct a strict System Prompt for the OpenAI API (using `gpt-4o-mini`). The prompt MUST force the AI to return ONLY a structured JSON object. 
5. The JSON structure must exactly match this schema:
   {
     "nodes": [
       { "id": "func1", "label": "functionName", "details": { "docs": "...", "refactoredCode": "...", "jestTest": "..." } }
     ],
     "edges": [
       { "source": "callerFuncId", "target": "calledFuncId" }
     ]
   }
6. Ensure the backend returns this parsed JSON safely to the client. Handle errors and timeouts properly.

