### Phase 3: Frontend - Flowchart Visualization (React Flow & Dagre)
This is the most critical and sensitive part.
1. On the `/result` page, initialize `reactflow`.
2. Since LLMs are bad at calculating X/Y coordinates, YOU MUST use the `dagre` layout algorithm to automatically position the nodes perfectly based on their edges. The flow should visually represent a top-down tree or hierarchy of functions.
3. Map the `nodes` from the AI response into React Flow node objects. Map the `edges` into React Flow edge objects.
4. Style the nodes using Tailwind to look professional and clickable. Add subtle CSS animations.

